        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 7 at 7:43AM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 740 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
McCrory, or 9 miles east of Augusta, moving east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Forrest City, Wynne, Madison, Village Creek State Park, Cherry
Valley, Caldwell, Colt, Widener, Hickory Ridge, Fair Oaks, Vanndale,
Hydrick, Birdeye, Cottonwood Corner, Slonikers Mill, Fitzgerald
Crossing, New Castle, Colton, McDonald, and Brushy Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
